      "writtenOn": "2026-06-09T14:18:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The whole reason for this migration is to get the Maven-style ergonomics: declare only the top-level deps and let `rules_jvm_external` pull in the transitive ones. Pinning every transitive artifact here defeats that purpose — the lockfile already handles version stability.\n\nYou\u0027ve found the three needed top level dependencies, used in BUILD file.\n\n```suggestion\n    artifacts \u003d [\n        \"io.github.azagniotov:dropwizard-metrics-cloudwatch:2.0.5\",\n        \"io.dropwizard.metrics:metrics-jvm:4.1.10.1\",\n        \"software.amazon.awssdk:cloudwatch:2.13.54\",\n    ],\n    duplicate_version_warning \u003d \"error\",\n```",
